01:11:25.670 --> 01:11:29.600
What people did talk about
in the context of CO2--

01:11:29.600 --> 01:11:32.780
so we talked about there
was a cap and trade bill.

01:11:32.780 --> 01:11:35.060
And environmentalists
said, well,

01:11:35.060 --> 01:11:37.670
the price could get so low there
wouldn't be any incentives.

01:11:37.670 --> 01:11:39.230
And industry said,
the price could

01:11:39.230 --> 01:11:41.390
be so high it would kill us.

01:11:41.390 --> 01:11:43.940
If we had sudden
economic growth,

01:11:43.940 --> 01:11:46.880
we could get really high prices
that would choke off growth.

01:11:46.880 --> 01:11:48.530
Or if the growth
was slow, you could

01:11:48.530 --> 01:11:50.405
have what you have in
Europe, which is really

01:11:50.405 --> 01:11:52.350
slow prices, really low prices.

01:11:52.350 --> 01:11:58.930
So people proposed, how about
we have a floor and a ceiling?

01:11:58.930 --> 01:12:02.920
The floor would be if the
price drops below this floor,

01:12:02.920 --> 01:12:06.620
some agency starts buying
these things on the market.

01:12:06.620 --> 01:12:08.680
If the price gets
above the ceiling,

01:12:08.680 --> 01:12:11.080
we start selling them
at the ceiling price.

01:12:11.080 --> 01:12:13.060
So you stand ready to
buy at the floor price

01:12:13.060 --> 01:12:16.315
and sell at the ceiling price
to limit the fluctuations.

01:12:16.315 --> 01:12:18.190
And if the floor and
ceiling are close enough

01:12:18.190 --> 01:12:21.840
together it looks like a tax.

01:12:21.840 --> 01:12:25.980
So that was a serious
set of proposals

01:12:25.980 --> 01:12:28.890
in the climate context
for exactly the reasons I

01:12:28.890 --> 01:12:30.300
think you're thinking of.

01:12:30.300 --> 01:12:35.010
Too low removes incentives;
too high is very expensive.

01:12:35.010 --> 01:12:38.010
You give up quantity
control, but you give up

01:12:38.010 --> 01:12:41.340
quantity control
sort of at the edges.

01:12:41.340 --> 01:12:46.690
If growth is really slow, then
emissions are going to be low.

01:12:46.690 --> 01:12:48.840
The problem is up here,
if growth is really fast,

01:12:48.840 --> 01:12:51.420
